description:
&lt;p&gt;X-Ray Clerk for the Emergency Department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Emergency Department administration team for an X-Ray Clerk. This post is based at the East Surrey site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary purpose of the role is to provide an efficient and effective in-box monitoring service for the Consultants within the Emergency Department (ED) in accordance with departmental guidelines, and to retrieve and input data on the Cerner/PACs systems. Also to provide administration support to our ED secretarial team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The X-Ray clerk will be expected to work as part of the ED Administration team, under the direction of the ED Service Delivery manager. You will be working closely with the ED Consultants and ED Secretaries. It is expected that by co-ordinating administrative tasks, and liaising with other departments, the post holder will contribute to the efficient and effective running of the ED.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is part time 23 hours per week. 7.5 hr Shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Jackie Sandford, Service Delivery manager on Ext 2484&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jackie Sandford&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Service Delivery Manage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: jackie.sandford@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01737 768511 x2484&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please report to the ED reception on the day of interview. - 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
